Growth Overview & Insights  
Ritual Hockey has generated $299,936.19 in total revenue year-to-date, reecting a 15.2%  
decline compared to the same period last year. Klaviyo-attributed owned revenue has  
dropped even further, down 17.7% to $96,710.41, now making up roughly 32.2% of total sales.  
This decline across both total and owned revenue indicates that current marketing strategies  
may not be keeping pace with business needs. The steeper drop in owned revenue suggests  
underutilisation of Klaviyos potential to drive retention and conversion. To reverse this trend, it  
will be critical to strengthen automation coverage, improve campaign targeting and  
engagement, and refocus on growing a high-quality subscriber base to stabilise and reignite  
top-line performance.

Year-to-date, Ritual Hockeys Klaviyo-attributed revenue has been led by ows, which brought  
in $66,306.81, contributing nearly 69% of owned revenue.  
Despite holding the larger revenue share, ow performance is down 22.9% compared to the  
same period last year. Campaigns, on the other hand, generated $30,403.60 in revenue (31%  
share), representing a more modest 3.5% decline year-over-year.  
Flow Performance Insights  
Flows have seen notable shifts in performance despite a 30.9% increase in total recipients,  
reaching 25.6K. Key metrics such as unique clicks (-9.2%), click rate (-30.9%), conversion rate  
(-27.8%), and revenue per recipient (-40.5%) have all declined.  
This drop in engagement and efciency suggests that while the audience reach has grown,  
the messaging or ow logic may no longer be compelling enough to drive meaningful action.  
Its possible the content is misaligned with recipient intent, or that saturation and fatigue are  
beginning to limit results. The dip in average order value by 16.6% also reinforces this potential  
disconnect between message and purchase motivation.  
Campaign Performance Insights  
Campaigns have seen similar headwinds, with declines across most key engagement metrics.  
Total recipients dropped 21.1%, and although open rate improved slightly by 6.8%, unique  
clicks are down 30.5% and click rate has decreased 11.9%.  
Conversion rate is low at just 0.108% (down 0.9%), with revenue per recipient falling 22.3%.  
While the revenue decline was less severe than in ows, campaign performance still indicates  
erosion in downstream engagement, likely caused by weakened targeting, creative fatigue, or  
poor alignment between email content and landing experience.  
What This Means for KAV Performance  
The combined declines in both engagement and conversion across ows and campaigns  
have contributed directly to the 17.7% YoY drop in owned revenue. The expanded reach in  
ows was not matched with improved message performance, resulting in diminishing  
returns. Campaigns had a smaller recipient pool this year and struggled to convert, despite  
stronger open rates. This suggests that while subject lines may be performing, the email body  
and CTAs need renement.  
To turn performance around, both ows and campaigns need a strategic refresh. For ows,  
focusing on segmentation, improving email content relevancy, and rening triggers will be  
key. For campaigns, optimising click-through elements, refreshing creative, and revisiting  
send timing and frequency will help recapture lost engagement. Together, these steps can  
help re-energise Ritual Hockeys owned-channel performance and regain positive  
momentum.

Creative & Testing: With a 30.5% drop in click rates, its time to refresh creative. Test stronger

Email list engagement [30 days]  
For the purpose of this list engagement audit, we created an All Active Proles segment, which  
includes every contact in your Klaviyo account who can be emailed - that is, proles that are not  
suppressed or bounced. However, it's important to note that being emailable in Klaviyo doesn't  
necessarily mean the contact has provided explicit marketing consent, especially in regions with  
stricter privacy regulations.  
Capturing engagement across your full list of active, non-suppressed proles offers a more  
comprehensive view of your subscriber base, ensuring the engagement report reects overall  
performance across all eligible recipients.  
The line graph below provides a visual snapshot of your databases engagement breakdown,  
showing the percentage of proles in each engagement level over the past 30 days. Note that the  
engagement report only encompasses the activity of the past 30 days. As a result, we are unable to  
generate a report covering the entire year to date.  
You will see proles organised into 5 buckets for each of your key lists:  
Very Engaged: Recipients who have a 50%+ open rate in the past 30 days.  
Somewhat Engaged: Recipients who have a 20-50% open rate in the past 30 days.  
Barely Engaged: Recipients who have an open rate that is greater than 0%, but less than 20%  
in the past 30 days.  
Not Engaged: Recipients who haven't opened any emails in the past 30 days.  
Received No Emails: Recipients who haven't received any emails in the past 30 days, likely  
because they're suppressed, old proles that you havent engaged with for a long time, or  
have recently been added to the list or segment.

Out of Ritual Hockeys 15,380 active proles, 56.99% are classied as Very Engaged and 3.32%  
as Somewhat Engaged, putting a strong 60.31% of the list in the top engagement tiers. This

However, 31.87% of the list is currently classied as Not Engaged, well above the

under Klaviyos billing model and drag down overall performance metrics.  
Suggested Next Steps  
Strategic Re-Engagement or List-Cleaning  
Given the recent manual suppressions and signs of acquisition fatigue across both  
email and SMS, we recommend launching targeted re-engagement campaigns to  
win back disengaged contacts before removing them. Routine suppression of  
inactives should continue, but in a way that allows for reactivation during high-intent  
periods like BFCM or major product launches.  
On SMS, with opt-out rates still low, theres an opportunity to test lighter  
re-engagement nudges (e.g. preference updates or exclusive early access) before  
escalating to suppression.  
Optimisation Tools  
An AI-powered tool like Orita.ai can help you manage this process more intelligently  
by identifying which inactive proles are worth saving, and which should be benched  
to protect deliverability and engagement.  
Orita.ai uses AI to:  
Identify true inactives vs. high-potential re-engagers. Orita analyses  
subscriber behavior to distinguish between those who might  
re-engage and those ready for suppression, ensuring you focus efforts  
on high-potential subscribers.  
Orita helps clean your list by agging problematic addresses, improving  
inbox placement and open rates.  
With data-driven insights, Orita recommends the best times and  
frequency to re-engage inactive subscribers without overwhelming  
them.  
If a subscriber is suppressed due to inactivity but decides to return later,  
Orita can automatically re-add them to your sending list. This ensures  
no potential engagement is lost and returning subscribers are  
welcomed back seamlessly.  
Orita leverages AI to segment unengaged subscribers, enabling you to  
create more effective win-back campaigns with personalised content  
and offers.  
Orita drops fresh AI-powered segments into Klaviyo so you can reach  
the right customer at the right time - maximising engagement without  
unnecessary email volume.

Suggested Improvement: Streamline Data Capture & Add Email Opt-In at VIP Sign-Up  
On the current VIP Program sign-up page, users are asked to enter their name and email  
address twice, once to create a Ritual Insider account, and again in the footer to subscribe to  
email news.  
This adds an extra step in the user journey, increasing the chance of drop-off and reducing  
newsletter sign-ups, especially among high-intent users who are likely to opt in if given the  
option upfront. If someone wants to join the VIP program, theyre also likely to want updates  
and offers, making this a missed opportunity to capture engaged subscribers.  
To streamline the experience and ensure clarity, we recommend adding a single,  
GDPR-compliant email marketing opt-in checkbox directly within the VIP Program sign-up  
form.  
Why This Matters:  
Reduces redundancy in the sign-up experience.  
Captures marketing consent at a high-intent moment (during VIP account  
creation).  
Keeps Ritual Hockey compliant with GDPR requirements for its UK-based  
customers.  
Helps grow the email list with qualied leads, without interrupting the user  
ow.  
Additional Data Capture Methods  
To grow the list beyond new visitor signups, we recommend expanding data capture methods to  
engage high-intent users at key touchpoints.  
This includes visitors browsing gear, abandoning checkout, or actively comparing products. By  
layering in targeted, behaviour-based forms, Ritual Hockey can better convert on-the-fence shoppers  
and collect more meaningful subscriber data to fuel personalisation.  
Here are three strategic tactics we could implement:  
Stick Finder Quiz (via Okendo Integration)  
Create an interactive quiz to help customers nd their ideal hockey stick based on  
position, playing style, skill level, and preferences (e.g., weight, balance, or grip).  
Data captured: Gear preference, playing level, position  
Use it for: Segmenting by product interest, serving personalized product recs, and  
driving higher intent ows (e.g., Your Perfect Stick email series)  
Exit-Intent Pop-Up  
An exit-intent pop-up is triggered when users move their cursor toward closing the  
browser or navigating away.  
This is a valuable opportunity to present a compelling message, such as reminding  
them of the 20% off offer, a unique value proposition, or a quick signup CTA, to convert  
hesitant visitors before they leave the site. Its especially effective for capturing  
abandoning trafc that hasnt yet converted or subscribed.  
Why it works: Most new visitors dismiss the initial pop-up because it appears too early,  
before theyve had a chance to explore. An exit-intent pop-up serves as a well-timed  
second chance that appears later in the journey when visitors are more engaged and  
closer to making a decision. At this stage, theyre more receptive to offers or  
value-driven messaging, increasing the likelihood of capturing the signup.  
Post-Purchase Preference Capture  
After checkout, prompt buyers to share a bit more:  
Thanks for your order! Want training tips, gear maintenance tips, or new  
product updates?  
Why it works: Youve earned their trustnow deepen the relationship with relevant  
content.  
Dataships  
Dataships is another excellent way to grow quality email and SMS leads. It is a data  
compliance and customer acquisition tool designed to help businesses grow their email and  
SMS lists while staying fully compliant with privacy laws like GDPR and CCPA.  
Essentially, Dataships streamlines the process of collecting rst-party data by embedding  
customisable forms on your website or checkout pages. These forms ensure all the necessary  
GDPR or CCPA compliance requirements are met, while still allowing you to grow your  
audience.  
These consent-driven forms prompt customers to provide their email addresses and phone  
numbers with clear value propositions, such as receiving order updates, tracking info, or  
exclusive perks like discounts and early access to sales. These are designed to comply with  
privacy laws, ensuring customers explicitly opt in to marketing communications.  
Why Dataships for Ritual Hockey:  
High-Intent, High-Value Audience  
Shoppers entering Ritual Hockeys checkout are already demonstrating strong  
purchase intent, making them far more likely to opt into email and SMS. These  
arent passive browsers; theyre engaged customers who are interested in your  
gear and ready to hear from you.  
Builds Trust with Players Worldwide  
As a brand serving both the US and UK, transparency around data usage is key.  
Dataships help Ritual Hockey clearly explain how customer data will be used,  
building trust and giving customers a sense of control. This not only supports  
compliance - it also increases opt-in and engagement rates.  
GDPR & CCPA Compliance Made Easy  
With a growing base of UK customers, GDPR compliance is non-negotiable.  
Dataships ensure all data capture - especially during checkout - is fully  
compliant with both GDPR and CCPA. This protects Ritual Hockey from  
potential nes and helps maintain a clean, consented list.  
Seamless Integration with Klaviyo  
Dataships syncs directly with Klaviyo, enabling immediate segmentation and

Theres a valuable opportunity to add a dedicated welcome email for new sign-ups to the  
Ritual VIP Program. This message can highlight the exclusive perks and benets of  
membership, helping to reinforce the value of joining while interest is high.  
Create a Welcome Flow for Ritual VIP Members  
Theres an opportunity to introduce a dedicated ow for subscribers who create an account  
and join the Ritual VIP Program. At present, this touchpoint isnt being leveraged, yet its a  
high-intent moment that deserves its own onboarding journey.  
A well-crafted ow here could start with a personalised welcome message for recent  
subscribers, followed by emails outlining the key benets of being a VIP member, how to  
make the most of their account, and exclusive access perks (like early drops, member-only  
offers, or tailored product recommendations).  
If the new VIP member is already an existing newsletter subscriber, the initial welcome  
message can be hidden or replaced with tailored content that acknowledges their familiarity  
with the brand, ensuring the messaging feels relevant and not repetitive.  
Tailor Content Based on Click Behaviour  
The current ow focuses heavily on sticks, which makes sense given theyre Rituals core  
product. However, this can inadvertently disengage subscribers who are more interested in  
other product categories like apparel or training equipment.  
Instead of taking a one-size-ts-all approach, we recommend adapting the experience using  
dynamic content or behavioural segmentation. For instance, if a subscriber clicks on  
equipment content, subsequent emails should reect that interest by highlighting benets,  
use-cases, and best sellers from that category.  
Using Dynamic Blocks for Personalisation  
For Ritual Hockey, where customers browse across multiple categories - like sticks, apparel,  
accessories, and Mens vs. Womens gear - personalising the welcome journey can  
signicantly boost early engagement.  
One effective strategy is using click-based interest tracking in the welcome emails. For  
example, if a new subscriber clicks on Womens or Mens in the email, that preference can  
be stored in their Klaviyo prole. Future emails can then dynamically adapt to showcase  
relevant collections - like performance apparel for women or stick recommendations for men.  
Example Execution: Utilizing Klaviyo's show/hide functionality, we displayed a tailored welcome  
hero image that aligns with the subscriber's shopping preferences (male, female, default).  
Reposition the Extended Discount Window  
While sending extended discount reminders on Day 9 and Day 10 is a great tactic, their  
timing in this case may be too late to effectively capture remaining purchase intent. Research  
shows that the rst 7 days post-signup are critical for converting new subscribers. Sending  
incentive reminders beyond this period risks reaching an audience thats already disengaged.  
We suggest testing a tripwire incentive or urgency-driven message on Day 7 to catch  
late-stage shoppers before intent drops off. Alternatively, bring the discount extension  
forward to land within the initial high-intent window.  
Abandoned cart  
A customer adding an item to their online shopping cart and almost completing checkout is a  
strong indication that they are interested in purchasing your product. But that sale doesnt always  
come to fruition immediately.  
A high-performing cart abandonment ow can be the difference between making the sale and  
losing it, whether your shopper forgot to complete their purchase, sought out options from another  
brand, or just didnt have their credit card nearby.  
Key Takeaways from Klaviyos 2024 Benchmarks Report  
Based on the performance data of all aggregated ecommerce industries, here are two key learnings  
about the Abandoned Cart ow:  
Abandoned cart ows drive the highest RPR and average placed order rate for all ows.  
If youre looking for a single ow to set up to drive revenue, youll nd it in the abandoned cart  
series.  
Theres the least disparity between the median and top 10% of conversions. This may tell us  
that few abandoned cart ows diverge from the standard, and there's not a huge amount of  
variety. It also may signal that you can't go wrong with even a standard abandoned cart ow.

Areas of Opportunity: Abandoned Cart  
Replace Text-Only Cart Reminders to Re-Engage Returning Customers  
A closer look at the ow setup reveals an opportunity in segmentation: the ow begins by  
splitting new and returning customers, and both groups currently receive a text-only email.  
While the text-only version for new customers is performing strongly with a 13% click rate YTD,  
the version for returning customers is driving 0% - indicating that this audience is not  
engaging with the current format.  
There are a few likely reasons for this: returning customers are already familiar with the brand  
and may expect a more polished, content-rich experience.  
A plain text email might feel underwhelming or easily overlooked in their inbox.  
Additionally, without visual cues or product imagery, theres nothing to remind them  
of what they left behind or reignite their interest.  
To address this, we recommend replacing the text-only version with a designed email that  
includes dynamic cart content, showcasing the exact items they abandoned. This makes the  
message more engaging and relevant, increasing the likelihood of clicks and conversions.  
Optimise for Click and Conversion Rate  
Currently, both the click rate (3.59%) and conversion rate (2.32%) are underperforming  
compared to the industry averages for Specialty (5.18% and 2.84% respectively). According to  
Klaviyos industry-wide data, the abandoned cart ow is typically one of the top  
revenue-generating automations - yet in this case, the ow isnt meeting that potential, and  
the revenue gap is substantial.  
When optimizing emails for clicks, weve seen strong results by incorporating personalization,  
making each message more relevant and engaging to the recipient.Here are a few impactful  
strategies we can implement to optimize abandoned cart emails and lift click-through  
performance:

Added to Cart vs. Started Checkout  
We observed that your only active abandoned cart ow is currently triggered by the "Started  
Checkout" event. To improve cart recovery efforts, we could introduce another cart recovery ow by  
using the "Added to Cart" trigger which targets customers earlier in their journey.  
Both triggers are effective for recapturing lost interest, but they target different stages in the  
customer journey. The Started Checkout ow tends to capture higher-intent customers who have  
progressed beyond the cart stage. Combining these approaches could help optimise recovery at  
multiple touchpoints.  
Here's how they differ:  
Added to Cart Trigger  
This is when a customer adds an item to their cart but does not proceed to checkout.  
Intent Level: Moderate. The customer is showing interest in a specic product but  
hasnt yet committed to starting the purchase process.  
Use Case: Great for sending gentle reminders about the product left in the cart, such  
as showcasing its value, adding urgency (e.g., low stock notications), or offering an  
incentive like free shipping.  
Started Checkout Trigger  
This is when a customer begins the checkout process, such as entering their contact,  
credit card details, and shipping information but does not complete the order.  
Intent Level: High. The customer is actively moving toward completing the purchase.  
Use Case: Ideal for targeting customers who are closer to conversion, focusing on  
removing barriers to checkout like payment options, shipping questions, or  
last-minute decision-making.  
Browse abandonment  
Sending an email ow to those who have left your website without purchasing is a strategic way to  
recapture some of those potential sales. This provides a key opportunity to re-engage casual  
browsers and move them further down the funnel, increasing the likelihood that they will add to cart,  
start checkout, or complete a purchase.

Additionally, Browse Abandonment ows tend to see higher click rates, suggesting that  
reminding visitors of the collections or products they were exploring is a powerful way to  
encourage them to return to the site and complete their purchase.

Other Browse-Intent Flows  
With the recent updates from Klaviyo, there are now several types of browse-intent ows that allow  
for more precise targeting of visitors at different stages of the funnel. Note that most of these  
features are available only to Shopify merchants.  
Collection Browse Abandonment Flow  
Trigger: This ow is triggered when a visitor views a product collection but doesn't  
engage with any specic items. It targets visitors who are exploring a broader category  
of products but may still be undecided or unsure about which item to focus on within  
the collection.  
Content: Since the visitor is exploring a wider selection, the email will focus on the  
collection as a whole. It may showcase bestsellers, popular products within that  
collection, or curated recommendations to reignite the visitors interest and guide  
them toward specic items that could lead to a purchase.  
Site Abandonment Flow  
Trigger: Activated when a visitor browses the site without viewing any products or  
collections. This is for those who may land on the homepage or a blog page but dont  
engage with specic collections or products.  
Content: The content for this ow will be more general, promoting key collections or  
new arrivals. Since the visitor hasnt shown specic interest, the goal is to spark broader  
interest with offerings that encourage them to explore further and engage with the  
site.  
Browse Search Flow (Triggered by Submitted Search)  
Trigger: This ow targets visitors who actively use the search bar on your site,  
indicating they have specic interests or needs but didnt take action afterward.  
Content: The email captures the keywords or phrases searched (e.g., searching for  
sticks, shin guards, or grips) and features products that match those terms. This  
ow aims to encourage the visitor to return and complete their purchase, increasing  
the likelihood of conversion.  
Post Purchase  
Essentially, after a customer completes a purchase, engagement shouldn't come to a halt. In fact, it's  
critical to maintain ongoing interaction with your customers, as research shows that the likelihood of  
a repeat customer making another purchase signicantly increases with each subsequent purchase.  
Therefore, during the post-purchase phase of a customer's journey, the primary objective should be  
to ensure a positive and enduring experience, fostering satisfaction and sustained engagement.  
Moreover, this series should serve as a guide, nudging the customer towards their next purchase.  
Key Takeaways from Klaviyos 2025 Benchmarks Report  
Based on the performance data of all aggregated ecommerce industries, here are some key  
learnings:  
Post-purchase ows have the highest ow open rate but lowest placed order rate. The  
immediate post-purchase experience is more about driving loyalty with your new customers  
than driving immediate purchases, though it's worth noting that the placed order rate is still  
higher than for email campaigns.  
In the post-purchase ow, you have your new customers attention. While an immediate  
additional purchase isnt going to happen every time, the post-purchase ow is certainly an  
opportunity to frame up-sell and cross-sell messages, in a sensitive and timely manner so as  
not to appear pushy.  
The top 10% of performers have achieved 4 times more purchases. By showcasing a greater  
variety of products in your post-purchase emails, we can stimulate repeat purchases in a  
shorter time frame.

Ritual Hockeys current campaign strategy targets a broad segment - Master Campaign
